<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-263-924  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 263 924.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  March 19 1990 v12 n12 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Northgate 486 system will cost same as many 386s. (the NorthgateComputer Systems Elegance 486-i 25 microcomputer) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Krohn, Nico; Copeland, Ron.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Northgate Computer Systems Inc (Plymouth, MN) introduces theNorthgate Elegance 486-i 25 microcomputer, a 25-MHz system basedon the 80486 microprocessor.andP;  An ISA version is available now, ata cost of $5,895 including monochrome monitor, with versionsdesigned for the Extended Industry Standard Architecture and theMicro Channel Architecture scheduled for fall 1990 release.andP;  Thestandard model of the Elegance 486-i 25 features 4Mbytes of RAM onthe motherboard, along with a 20-Mbyte hard disk drive and both3.5-inch and 5.25-inch floppy disk drives.andP;  The machine comesequipped with monochrome monitor, but an optional Super VGA colormonitor providing 1,024 by 768 pixels resolution is available in apackage that costs $6,695.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Northgate Computer Systems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Northgate Computer Systems Elegance 486 25i (Microcomputer)(product introduction)Intel 80486 (Microprocessor) (usage).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMicrocomputers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>